PN,32702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F327A1784047674
OL,3,CDog gets Stranraer lifeboat VIP
OL,4,Ctreatment during medical emergency
OL,6,FThe volunteer crew say they quickly
OL,7,Flocated the casualty vessel, which had
OL,8,Frun aground while the tide was low.
OL,9,FAfter assessing the boat and its
OL,10,Foccupants, everyone was found to be
OL,11,Fsafe and well at that time. They
OL,12,Fattempted to assist but the tide was
OL,13,Ftoo low to safely re-float it so the
OL,14,Fcrew stood down and returned to the
OL,15,Flifeboat station.
OL,17,FThe situation changed however, when
OL,18,Fthey received another call at around
OL,19,F19.45 and a full crew relaunched to
OL,20,Fattend the boat again.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,328,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F327A1784047674
OL,3,CDog gets Stranraer lifeboat VIP
OL,4,Ctreatment during medical emergency
OL,6,FOne of the men onboard was found to be
OL,7,Fsuffering a medical emergency. RNLI
OL,8,Fcasualty care was provided and he was
OL,9,Ftaken ashore to Stranraer Harbour, to
OL,10,Fthe care of Stranraer Coastguard
OL,11,FRescue Team and the Scottish Ambulance
OL,12,FService.
OL,14,FThe casualty's dog was also safely
OL,15,Ftaken ashore to Stranraer Marina by
OL,16,Fthe lifeboat crew and reunited with
OL,17,Fits owner.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,328,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F327A1784047674
OL,3,CDog gets Stranraer lifeboat VIP
OL,4,Ctreatment during medical emergency
OL,6,FThe evening high tide was expected at
OL,7,Faround 10pm so the crew then returned
OL,8,Fto the vessel, which was now afloat so
OL,9,Fthe crew were able to tow it into
OL,10,FStranraer Marina.
OL,12,FStranraer RNLI wished the casualty a
OL,13,Ffull and speedy recovery.
OL,15,FA spokesperson for Stranraer RNLI
OL,16,Fsaid, "This incident demonstrates how
OL,17,Fquickly a routine service call can
OL,18,Fchange.
OL,26,@xD@GOU
